transcription.text:
Speaker 1: I'd like to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 2: Okay, let me pull your prescription here, okay?

Speaker 1: Mr. Charles Miller?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Yes, you have a prescription, I think it's Viagra 100mg, 10 tablets, and I think they—

Speaker 2: Got you on a 30-day supply.

Speaker 1: Any health concern, or you just want to order as needed?

Speaker 2: You want to cancel the 30 days?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay, I'm going to cancel the initial writing.

Speaker 1: They usually write it this way when you order only 10, because there's 30 days in a month,

Speaker 2: assuming that if you need Viagra, you're active with your wife or your girlfriend or whatever.

Speaker 1: But I'm going to cancel that for you, pause the prescription, they pause it up to half—

Speaker 2: A year, so that way I can keep you at the same price, you don't pay a higher price,

Speaker 1: and if you just maintain to refill a year, you can keep that price as well, okay?

Speaker 2: But I'm going to stop the 30-day supply, okay?

Speaker 1: Alright.

Speaker 2: Alright, you'll be all set, okay?

Speaker 1: You'll be paused for half a year, prescription is available, okay?

Speaker 2: But not every single month anymore.

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: Alright, so you're all set.

Speaker 1: You're all set, okay?

Speaker 2: I'll pause you.

Speaker 1: Alright, thank you.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
